                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 337.11/203</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Gonzales</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-01T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 1, 1917, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Protection for the following properties, owned by Americans, is urged by those
                    interested therein: Guantanamo and Western Railroad Company; Santa Cecilia Sugar
                    Company; La Maya Valley Land and Improvement Company; Ermita Sugar Company;
                    Confluente Sugar Company; Guantanamo City Land and Development Company, all
                    located in Oriente Province.</p>
                <p>You will request the Cuban Government to have these properties properly
                    guarded.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
